## Description

This report presents the results of **Litmus Chaos** experiments run against a
Kubernetes cluster to evaluate system resilience. Each experiment injects a specific
fault (e.g. pod deletion, network latency, CPU/memory stress, DNS errors) into a
target workload and observes whether the system recovers correctly.

**Success criteria**: Each experiment's ChaosResult verdict must be "Pass" with a
probe success percentage of 100%, indicating the system handled the injected fault
as expected.

